<title>HONG KONG: China Merchants 1996 net rises 38 pct.</title>
<headline>China Merchants 1996 net rises 38 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million US$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (U.S. cents)	   7.9	 vs  5.7</p>
<p>    Dividend (U.S. cents)    5.0	 vs  4.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  2.61 gain vs  0.41 loss</p>
<p>    Net			    7.49	vs  5.42</p>
<p>    Turnover		     6.91	vs  7.27</p>
<p>    Company name		 China Merchants China Direct</p>
<p>				     Investments Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  June 13-18</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   July 8</p>
<p>NOTE - China Merchants China Direct is a closed-end investment company.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional gain of US$1.33 million on disposal of subsidiaries, gain of US$1.49 million on disposal of listed investments and loss of US$210,000 on revaluation of listed investments.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is six U.S. cents (including interim dividend of one cent) vs five cents.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
</text>
